and Painter perhaps) and Maya (and 3d studio Max perhaps) respectively. As well as of course, drawing in general. <br>
<br>
Now I notice sometimes you guys talk about tablets, we have them at my college, and a few of my friends use them. I am wondering for those of you who have one or plan to get one...whats the deal with them? Do they make digital inking and coloring alot easier? Whats a good one for a home user? Etc etc post your advice on tablets.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=temporaryinsanity@polykarbonbbs>temporary insanity</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/27/03 11:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12707.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Honing my skills in 2d art...whats up with Tablets?</span><hr size=1> well depends, i use Nisis G6 which is rather big (A3)(you can get smaller ones)<br>
and has 512 levels of preesure. comes with a mouse aswell and handwriting recognition.<br>
<br>
there are wacoms aswell but i have not tried it.<br>
i strongly suggest looking into them. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.angelfire.com/anime5/ghl/neoghl.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ohhenry18>ohhenry18</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/27/03 3:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12707.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www3.telus.net/nhung/me1.gif length=26 width=29></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Honing my skills in 2d art...whats up with Tablets?</span><hr size=1> Tablets make digial painting a hell of a lot easier, mainly because of the pressure sensitivity.  Its almost impossible to do a good digital painting without a tablet.  As for photoshopping and such, i can basically do the same thing with a mouse, it just that the tablet makes things easier and faster.<br>
<br>
If you are lookin into getting a tablet i would strongly suggest a wacom (<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.wacom.com)">www.wacom.com)</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>- I see things how they are, not how they're supposed to be -</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=retrotorque>RetroTorque</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/28/03 12:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12707.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Honing my skills in 2d art...whats up with Tablets?</span><hr size=1> They make digital coloring and inking easier if you already possess the skills required to draw, ink, and color. If you don't understand color, a tablet will help you no more than sheet of paper and a marker. Ditto for drawing and inking. I add the bit about understanding what you're doing because there are people who think and say &quot;if I had a tablet I could draw/ink/color/paint good too.&quot; The tablet is just a tool. What you get from it is what you bring from practice.<br>
<br>
As for a good one: I currently have a wacom intous 2 6x8 tablet. I think it's the best investment I've ever made in terms of my art supplies... after my sketchbooks. I've had if for a full year now and it's still as responsive and precise as it was the day I got it out of the box. <p>Be well, do good work, and keep in touch. -Writer's Almanac NPR</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gaarasunakage>Gaara Sunakage</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/gaara_sunakage/Orochimaru.txt" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/28/03 9:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12707.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://godkodiak.homestead.com/files/Gaara1.jpg height=79 width=130></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Honing my skills in 2d art...whats up with Tablets?</span><hr size=1> I have a wacom 5X6 or something close to that, it makes cg alot easier. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/gaara_sunakage/NARUTOdraw.txt" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pencilsoldier>Pencil Soldier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/29/03 7:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12707.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.freewebs.com/pencilsoldier/pencils.txt  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Honing my skills in 2d art...whats up with Tablets?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZC